cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with shape retrieval of 3D human models, which is a common problem in computer graphics and vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves benchmarking and testing of algorithms, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of 3D models and scans suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for shape retrieval, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
